Sentencas: Ni-Fe-alloy-foam supported solid oxide electrolysis cell with an arrangement of nickle and Sc0.1Ce0.005Gd0.005Zr0.89O2 (Ni-SCGZ) cathode, SCGZ electrolyte and Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) anode is successfully fabricated by the sequence wet-chemical coating.
Titulo: Fabrication using sequence wet-chemical coating and electrochemical performance of Ni-Fe-foam-supported solid oxide electrolysis cell for hydrogen production from steam

Sentencas: The multilayer cathode with a gradient of thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) is deposited on the alloy-foam support.
Titulo: Fabrication using sequence wet-chemical coating and electrochemical performance of Ni-Fe-foam-supported solid oxide electrolysis cell for hydrogen production from steam

Sentencas: Two-step firing processes are applied including cathode pre-firing (1373 K, 2 h) and electrolyte sintering (1623 K, 4 h) using slow heating rate enhanced with compressive loading.
Titulo: Fabrication using sequence wet-chemical coating and electrochemical performance of Ni-Fe-foam-supported solid oxide electrolysis cell for hydrogen production from steam

Sentencas: The fabricated cell shows current density of -0.95 Acmb(-2) at 1.1 V with H2O:H-2 = 70:30 and 1073 K, providing hydrogen production rate at 4.95 x 10(-6) mol s(-1).
Titulo: Fabrication using sequence wet-chemical coating and electrochemical performance of Ni-Fe-foam-supported solid oxide electrolysis cell for hydrogen production from steam

Sentencas: However, performance degradation was observed with the rate of 0.08 V h(-1), which can be ascribed to the delamination of BSCF anode under operating at high current density.
Titulo: Fabrication using sequence wet-chemical coating and electrochemical performance of Ni-Fe-foam-supported solid oxide electrolysis cell for hydrogen production from steam
